description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Band 3 Emergency Care Technician (ECT) to join our existing team of motivated and innovative nurses in the Children&#39;s Emergency Care Unit at City Hospital. This role will be working alongside the doctors and nurses in assisting with the initial diagnostics and on going treatment of children attending the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a dynamic, busy Emergency Department offering a wide range of clinical experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic, motivated individuals to join our team in this dynamic and busy department, as we continue to develop patient led services and expand roles that reflect the on-going changes in Emergency healthcare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ECT role involves working closely with the nursing team to develop patient centred services and carry out all basic healthcare duties. This role also provides you with an excellent opportunity to use and develop your existing skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience in a hospital health care environment is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This position is to provide cover during the hours of 12 midday until 12 midnight, 365 days a year, including weekends and Bank Holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMarie HinksJob titleUnit LeadEmail addressmarie.hinks@nhs.netTelephone number0121 507 4467Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can also contact Matron Annabel Bottrill&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0121 507 5453&lt;/p&gt;
